urlLink How to Find Information in the Information Age  This is a new library lesson plan at LibraryInstruction.Com.  It is written by Jeanne Guthrie and geared towards 4th, 5th, 6th, 7th, and 8th grade students.  Description:  This unit of study will ask students to become familiar with the Dewey Decimal System, the many different sources of information available in libraries, and how technology can be used in the research process. It will utilize web links to teach the way information is organized in a library and how students can find the data that they need for reports or just to satisfy a curiosity.